---

<ResearchLayout title="Active Rigging 2026 - Election Rigging" description="Trump is actively attempting to rig the 2026 midterm elections through FBI raids, voting machine seizures, calls to 'nationalize voting,' and federal takeover of state elections.">

  <SeriesNav tabs={electionTabs} currentPath="/election-rigging/rigging-2026" />

  <Breadcrumbs items={[
    { label: 'Research', href: '/' },
    { label: 'Election Rigging', href: '/election-rigging' },
    { label: 'Active Rigging 2026' }
  ]} />

  <Masthead
    eyebrow="Part 3 of 3 · Election Rigging"
    title="2026: RIGGING BEFORE THE VOTE"
    titleHighlight="RIGGING"
    subtitle="Unlike 2020, Trump is attempting to rig elections before votes are even cast"
    date="Last Updated: March 4, 2026"
    eyebrowColor="var(--red-bright)"
  />

  <Ticker items={tickerItems} />

  <HighlightBar text="THESE ACTIONS ARE HAPPENING RIGHT NOW" variant="red" />

  <IntroQuote
    quote="This is happening right now. Unlike 2020 (attempting to overturn after losing), Trump is attempting to rig the 2026 midterms before votes are even cast. This is documented, real-time election rigging through federal law enforcement, unconstitutional takeover attempts, and systematic dismantling of oversight."
    citation="Evidence-Based Documentation"
  />

  <!-- What Trump Said - 2026 -->
  <VoicesSection
    eyebrow="2026 · What Trump Said"
    title="Stated<br>Intentions"
    introText="Trump's stated intentions for 2026 elections"
  >
    <VoiceCard
      quote="We should take over the voting in at least — many, 15 places. The Republicans ought to nationalize the voting."
      attribution="Donald Trump — February 2, 2026 (Dan Bongino Show) · Called for Republicans to &quot;nationalize voting&quot; and federally take over elections in 15 states. Named Detroit, Philadelphia, and Atlanta as &quot;extremely corrupt&quot; (all Democratic-leaning cities, no evidence). Constitutional violation: Article 1, Section 4 grants states, not the federal government, power over elections. · <a href='https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2026/02/02/trump-elections-nationalize-fraud/' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>Washington Post</a> | <a href='https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/trump-midterm-election-results-voting-nationalize-b2914259.html' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>The Independent</a>"
    />
    <VoiceCard
      quote="I will, if the elections are honest. If the elections aren't honest, then something else has to happen."
      attribution="Donald Trump — February 5, 2026 (NBC's Tom Llamas) · On accepting 2026 midterm results. Pre-emptive fraud claim — setting up to reject results if Republicans lose. In same interview, lied about using the word &quot;nationalize&quot; despite being recorded saying it 3 days earlier. Pattern: 2020 lost = fraud. 2024 won = no fraud. 2026 = setting up fraud claims if Republicans lose. · <a href='https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/trump-midterm-election-results-voting-nationalize-b2914259.html' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>The Independent</a> | <a href='https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/trump-urges-republicans-nationalize-voting/story?id=129793658' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>ABC News</a>"
    />
    <VoiceCard
      quote="If Democrats don't want voter ID, if they don't want voter ID, that means they want to cheat. We can't allow cheating in elections."
      attribution="Donald Trump — February 5, 2026 · Deflecting from his &quot;nationalize&quot; comments by claiming Democrats &quot;want to cheat.&quot; From the man who asked Georgia Secretary of State to &quot;find&quot; 11,000+ votes in 2020. · <a href='https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/us-politics/trump-midterm-election-results-voting-nationalize-b2914259.html' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>Source: The Independent</a>"
    />
    <VoiceCard
      quote="You're damn right we're going to have ICE surround the polls come November"
      attribution="Steve Bannon — February 5, 2026 · White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt: &quot;I can't guarantee that an ICE agent won't be around a polling location in November.&quot; ILLEGAL: Federal and state laws prohibit federal law enforcement at polling places. Intent: suppress voter turnout through intimidation. Senator Bernie Sanders called Trump a &quot;demagogue&quot; and &quot;authoritarian.&quot; · <a href='https://thehill.com/homenews/media/5723066-bannon-ice-presence-polls/' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>The Hill</a> | <a href='https://www.democracydocket.com/news-alerts/steve-bannon-says-ice-will-surround-the-polls-as-trump-doubles-down-on-taking-over-elections/' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>Democracy Docket</a> | <a href='https://www.newsweek.com/warnings-issued-on-nationalizing-elections-ice-at-polls-huge-danger-11467048' target='_blank' rel='noreferrer' style='color: var(--red);'>Newsweek</a>"
    />
