      title="FBI Raids Georgia Elections Office — Gabbard Present, Calls Trump During Raid"
      description="Jan 28: FBI raided Fulton County (Atlanta) elections office. Seized 700 boxes of 2020 ballots, tabulator tapes, voter rolls, ballot images. Based on Trump's false claims about 2020 fraud. DNI Tulsi Gabbard physically present (unprecedented). Gabbard used cellphone to call Trump during raid (per congressional letter). Gabbard's presence illegal: DNI prohibited from domestic law enforcement. Jan 29: Trump ordered Gabbard to Atlanta. She arranged call between Trump and FBI agents. Trump spoke on speakerphone praising agents for raiding election office. Officials described it as a 'pep talk.' Raid affidavit remains sealed."
    />
    <TimelineItem
      date="MAY 2025"
      badge="SEVERE"
      badgeType="catastrophic"
      title="Gabbard's DNI Illegally Seizes Puerto Rico Voting Machines"
      description="DNI Gabbard's office obtained Puerto Rico voting machines, investigating alleged Venezuelan hacking. US Attorney, HSI, and FBI 'facilitated voluntary turnover' of voting hardware to ODNI. Three Reuters sources confirmed goal was investigating Venezuela hacking claims. NO EVIDENCE found of foreign interference. Sen. Mark Warner: 'Absent a foreign nexus, intelligence agencies have absolutely no lawful role in domestic election administration. This is exactly the kind of overreach Congress wrote the law to prevent.' Puerto Rico doesn't vote in presidential elections — likely a testing ground for seizing machines before targeting states."
    />
    <TimelineItem
      date="JAN 2026"
      badge="SEVERE"
      badgeType="catastrophic"
      title="Pam Bondi Grants Missouri Prosecutor Nationwide 2020 Election Investigation"
      description="AG Pam Bondi granted a Missouri prosecutor special authority to investigate 2020 election matters nationwide — far beyond Missouri's jurisdiction. Creates roving federal prosecutor focused on Trump's 2020 election grievances, expanding investigation of already-adjudicated claims that 60+ courts rejected."
    />
    <TimelineItem
      date="JAN 2026"
      badge="SEVERE"
      badgeType="catastrophic"
      title="Minnesota: DOJ Conditions Federal Agent Withdrawal on Voter Data"
      description="AG Pam Bondi conditioned withdrawal of federal agents from Minnesota on the state providing sensitive voter data to the Trump administration. Federal law enforcement presence used as leverage to extract state voter information — classic authoritarian tactic. DOJ using federal agents as bargaining chips to force states to surrender voter data."
    />
    <TimelineItem
      date="MAR 2026"
      badge="SEVERE"
      badgeType="catastrophic"
      title="Trump Allies Push Emergency Powers for 2026 Midterms — Federal Agents to Polls"
      description="Trump allies openly pushing to invoke emergency powers ahead of November 2026 midterms. Proposals include: deploying federal agents including ICE and potentially National Guard to polling places, seizing state election infrastructure under emergency declarations, overriding state election laws by federalizing election oversight. Dramatic escalation beyond earlier refusal to rule out ICE at polls. Senate Democrats preparing legislative measures to block. Posse Comitatus Act of 1878 prohibits use of federal military at polls. Constitutional scholars: using emergency powers to interfere with elections would be unprecedented."
    />
    <TimelineItem
      date="JAN 2026"
      badge="SEVERE"
      badgeType="catastrophic"
      title="DOJ Sues 23+ States for Voter Rolls Including Sensitive Personal Data"
      description="Trump's DOJ filed lawsuits against 23 states plus D.C. demanding complete voter registration lists including: full names, home addresses, Social Security numbers, mothers' maiden names, dates of birth, tribal ID numbers, driver's license information, complete voting history. California alone: DOJ sought data of nearly 23 million Californians. Arizona Secretary of State Fontes: 'This administration is weaponizing law enforcement for the purpose of satisfying the president's obsession with his 2020 election loss.' Multiple states refused, citing laws prohibiting sharing confidential voter data."
    />
