        <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Kash Patel (FBI Director)</strong> — Compiled "enemies list," publicly threatened investigations of journalists and Trump critics</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Tulsi Gabbard (DNI)</strong> — Illegally coordinated FBI raid, amplified Russian propaganda, no intelligence experience</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Todd Blanche (Acting AG)</strong> — Trump's personal criminal defense lawyer now running DOJ</li>
        <li><strong style="color: var(--text);">Dan Bongino (FBI Deputy)</strong> — Talk radio host, no FBI experience, built career defending Trump on air</li>
      </ul>
      <p style="margin: 0;"><a href="/attacking-democracy/installing-loyalists" style="color: var(--red-bright); text-decoration: underline; font-weight: 600;">Read Full Documentation: Installing Loyalists</a></p>
    </AlertBanner>
  </ColoredSection>

  <!-- Related: Purging Oversight -->
  <ColoredSection background="#0a0a14" borderColor="var(--blue)">
    <AlertBanner icon="🔗" title="Related: Purging Oversight" variant="blue">
      <p style="font-size: 15px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 12px;">Trump's firing of 17 Inspector Generals (ruled unlawful) removed oversight of DOJ/FBI, enabling coordination of the Georgia raid and election interference with no accountability mechanism.</p>
      <ul style="margin-left: 1.2rem; margin-bottom: 12px;">
        <li>No IG to investigate FBI's political coordination</li>
        <li>No whistleblower protections for agents who object</li>
        <li>Loyalists like Kash Patel (FBI) and Tulsi Gabbard (DNI) operate without oversight</li>
