    />
    <TimelineItem
      date="JAN 15, 2026"
      badge="DISMISSED"
      badgeType="serious"
      title="Federal Judge Dismisses DOJ Voter Roll Lawsuit — &quot;Unprecedented and Illegal&quot;"
      description="U.S. District Judge David O. Carter (California) dismissed DOJ lawsuit seeking voter data from 23 million Californians. Judge Carter: 'The taking of democracy does not occur in one fell swoop; it is chipped away piece-by-piece until there is nothing left. The case before the Court is one of these cuts that imperils all Americans.' Dismissed without leave to amend — signal DOJ's legal theory is fundamentally flawed. Oregon district judge indicated similar ruling planned."
    />
