    />
    <VoiceCard
      quote="The Georgia raid is pre-rigging. They're not waiting to lose and then contest — they're seizing control of the election apparatus before votes are cast. This is how democracies die."
      attribution="Timothy Snyder — Yale Historian · February 2026 · Source: Substack"
    />
  </VoicesSection>

  <!-- 2026 Escalation -->
  <ColoredSection background="#120a0a" borderColor="var(--red)">
    <AlertBanner icon="🚨" title="The 2026 Escalation" variant="red">
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7;"><strong style="color: var(--text);">2020:</strong> Trump tried to overturn an election <strong style="color: var(--red-bright);">after losing</strong>.</p>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7;"><strong style="color: var(--text);">2026:</strong> Trump is trying to control elections <strong style="color: var(--red-bright);">before votes are cast</strong>.</p>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px;">This is not about Trump believing elections are rigged. <strong style="color: var(--text);">This is about Trump rigging elections.</strong></p>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 12px;">The coup didn't work, so he's trying a different approach: Use federal power to seize control of election systems before there's anything to overturn. If he controls who counts the votes, who oversees the elections, and who certifies the results — he doesn't need a coup. He just needs to call it an election.</p>
